   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>OUTLINE FOUR PRACTICAL FELLOWSHIP CONCERNING</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>THE LORD'S TABLE MEETING Scripture Reading: John 6:35, 57; Psa 116:12-14; 1 John 1:7, 9; Rev 1:10; Psa 118:24; 84:1-2; 42:4; 100:4; 96:8; Heb 13:15; Psa 50:23; 116:17; Rev 5:13; Psa 8:2; Matt 21:16; Luke 22:19a; Psa 89:7; Heb 12:28; Deut 14:23 Our eating, drinking, and enjoying the Lord at His supper are our declaration and testimony.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Our declaration is that we are joined to the Lord and mingled with Him, just as the bread becomes mingled with us after being received into our body.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Our testimony is that we live by eating, drinking and enjoying the Lord, taking Him as our life every day.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>The significance of eating the bread and drinking the cup is actually the significance of the Christian life; the Christian life is a life of daily eating, drinking, and enjoying the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>We need to prepare ourselves for the Lord's table meeting.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>We should maintain a holy diet by eating Jesus daily as the bread of life John 6:35, 57 to be renewed day by day morning by morning by being nourished with the fresh supply of the resurrection life 2 Cor 4:16 pray-reading the Word and reading the ministry that opens up the Word.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>We should drink the cup of blessing, the cup of salvation, continually throughout the day 1 Cor 10:16; Psa 116:12-14, 17 calling on the name of the Lord conversing with the Lord, thanking the Lord, and praising the Lord .</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>We should enjoy the continuous and constant cleansing of the Lord's blood throughout the day 1 John 1:7, 9 confessing our sins.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>We should prepare our being for the Lord's table meeting on the Lord's day: By beginning the day in the evening before the Lord's day morning Gen 1:5b; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Lev 23:32.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>By exercising ourselves to be in spirit on the Lord's day Rev 1:10; Acts 20:7; Psa 118:24.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>When we are intending to go to the meeting, we must spend some time to pray for at least five to ten minutes.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>In our prayer, we should confess our sins to the Lord to enjoy the filling of the Holy Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>We must learn to abide in the fellowship with the Lord.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>The enemy tries to frustrate us either from coming to the meeting or from coming to the meeting in a prepared state.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>We should get ourselves prepared to speak in the meeting, to praise the Lord 1 Cor 14:26.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>We should not "leave the meeting to fortune" but come prepared by and with the Lord to bear the meeting just as the priests bore the ark; the meeting is the ark, the testimony.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>We should come to the Lord's table meeting in a recovered way: With a love for the meetings Psa 84:1-2.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In newness Matt 26:29.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>With a voice of joy and praise Psa 42:4.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>With thanksgiving and praise Psa 100:4.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>With some offerings Psa 96:8.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Being punctual.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>Coming to the front to take care of the meeting as fighting soldiers to conquer the enemy and as prepared athletes to win the game.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Standing against our natural disposition, leaving our self with all emotional feelings outside the door, and exercising our spirit to sense the Lord and to praise and thank the Lord.</S>
   </TEXT>
